<li><p>
<a name = "mit">
<h3>Special Issue of <b><I>Serials Librarian</I></b> to be Devoted to Electronic Journals </h3>
<I><font size = -1>Wayne Jones<br>
Head of Serials Cataloging, MIT Libraries<br>
Cambridge, Massachusetts
</font></I>
<p>
A new book about electronic serials is scheduled to be published by Haworth Press
next spring.  The book, a special issue of <b>Serials Librarian</b>, includes articles on a wide range of topics, including: publishing, pricing, copyright, acquisitions and collection
development, cataloging and metadata, preservation and archiving,
descriptions of various local/national/international projects, indexing,
uniform resource identifiers, and citation. For more information, including
abstracts of the articles, see the website at
&lt;<A HREF = "http://web.mit.edu/waynej/www/onlineserials.htm">http://web.mit.edu/waynej/www/onlineserials.htm</a>&gt;, or contact the editor,
Wayne Jones, at <A HREF = "mailto:waynej@mit.edu">waynej@mit.edu</a>. The full-text of a few of the articles will
also be posted to the site over the next months.
<p>
</UL>
<UL>
<A NAME = "RLG">
<li></a>
<A HREF = "http://www.rlg.org/meta9707.html">Metadata Summit:  Meeting Report</a>, Willy Cromwell-Kessler and Ricky Erway. 
<br>
This report summarizes an invitational "summit meeting" on metadata issues organized by the Research Libraries Group on July 1, 1997.  The "summit" proposed to identify metadata issues with
special relevance for the research community in order to formulate, if possible, a common action agenda. Discussion was centered on the potential role of the Dublin Core elements as a
mechanism for discovery of information resources available via the
Internet, but which are not static HRML-Web pages.  
</UL>
<P>
<UL>
<A NAME = "WIZARDS">
<li></a>
Network Wizards, Menlo Park, California, has released its semi-annual 
<A HREF = "http://www.nw.com/zone/WWW/report.html">survey results</a> (July 1997) on the size of the Internet.  The report includes various tabular summaries based on top-level domain and host names as well as the authors' observations.
</UL>
<p>
<UL><A NAME = "ELECTRONIC">
<LI></A>
The <A HREF = "http://www.si.umich.edu/e-recs/">final report</a> from the 1996 conference on research and development in electronic records, sponsored by the University of Michigan, School of Information and the Bentley Historical Library, has been posted together with the conference agenda.  The report addresses issues in archiving, preservation, and related technologies.
</ul>
<p>
<UL>
<A NAME = "ALLIANCE">
<LI></A>
The Regional Alliance for Preservation is a one-year project involving four participants: the Upper Midwest Conservation Association, National Endowment for the Humanities, AMIGOS Preservation Service, Northeast Document Conservation Center, and Southeastern Library Network Preservation Services.  The Alliance is testing two methods for collaborating:  sharing training materials through a newsletter, and sharing equivalent information via a 
<A HREF = "http://www-cpa.stanford.edu/cpa/misc/rap/">web site</a>.
</ul>
