<H3><A NAME="goingson">Goings On</A></H3>
<P>
<UL>
<A NAME = "ASIDIC">
<LI>The </A> Fall 1997 meeting of the 
<A HREF = "http://www.accessinn.com/seattl~1.htm">Association of Information and Dissemination Centers (ASIDIC)</a> will meet in Seattle, Washington, October 21-23, 1997.  The program covers a number of issues relating to information management including databases, metadata, search, and simulation technologies.
<p>
</UL>
<UL>
<A NAME = "TORONTO">
<LI></A>
<A HREF = "http://citd.scar.utoronto.ca/EPub/agenda.html">Beyond Print: Scholarly Publishing and Communication in the Electronic Environment</a> will be held at the University of Toronto at Scarborough, Canada, September 26-27, 1997.  The conference will deal with a number of issues related to the economics of publishing, peer review and quality control, the role of government agencies and university administrators, accessibility, intellectual property, and retrieval,
archiving, and technology.<p>
</ul> 
<ul>
<a name = "CONFU">
<LI></a><A HREF = "http://oregon.uoregon.edu/~csundt/pdx.htm">Copyright Law in the Digital World:  Fair Use, Education and Libraries after CONFU (The Conference on Fair Use)</a> is a "town meeting" to be held on the campus of Reed College in Portland, Oregon, September 27, 1997.  This is the fourth in a series of programs supported by the Samuel H. Kress Foundation to help educators, librarians, and other interested parties learn more about the CONFU process, the proposed guidelines, and fair use.
<p>
</ul>
<ul>
<a name = "AMIA">
<li></a>The Fall 1997 Symposium for the 
<A HREF = "http://www.amia.org/f97flyer.html">American Medical Informatics Association (AMIA)</a> will meet in Nashville, Tennessee, October 25-29, 1997.  The themes of the conference are "The Emergence of 'Internetable' Health Care" and "Systems That Really Work!"  Individual sessions are devoted to Java implementation, clinical information systems, data mining and software agents, and ethical challenges.
 <p>
</ul>
<UL>
<A NAME = "INFORMATION">
<LI></A>
<a href = " http://panizzi.shef.ac.uk/david_allen/ISIC/isic.html">Information Seeking in Context: an International Conference on Information Needs, Seeking and Use in  Different Contexts</a> will be held August 13-15, 1998 in Sheffield, UK.  The Call for Proposals closes October 31, 1997.  Details on submission as well as information on the program, registration, and accommodations are available through the web site.
</UL>
<p>
<ul>
<A NAME = "TEI">
<li>
</a>The 
<A HREF = "http://www.stg.brown.edu/webs/tei10/index.html">Text Encoding Initiative:  Tenth Anniversary User Conference</a> will be held at Brown University in Providence, Rhode Island, from November 14 -to November 16, 1997.  Although the event celebrates 10 years of work within the TEI, this is the first users conference that has been organized. Topics to be covered include but are not limited to the following:

<UL>
<LI>use of the TEI scheme in a particular project or in a particular application area or discipline

<LI>interests of various user communities (e.g., builders and designers of electronic text centers, digital libraries, language corpora, electronic editions, multi-media databases, etc.)

<LI>evaluation in the context of a particular class of texts or in a given type of scholarly research

<li>encoding problems and solutions that have arisen or may arise, such as unusual or complex text types, multi-media, multiple views or information types, multi-lingual data and internationalization, textual variation, overlap, etc.

<LI>customization and extension of the TEI for particular application areas and text types

<LI>experiences based on  using off-the-shelf software with TEI documents, or developing software to handle TEI material

<LI>markup theory and markup architectures
</UL>
</UL>
<p>
